item.title: Single Linked List
item.description: What is Linked List? When we want to work with an unknown number of data values, we use a linked list data structure to organize that data. The linked list is a linear data structure that contains a sequence of elements such that each element links to its next element in the sequence. Each element in a linked list is called “Node”. What is Single Linked List? Simply a list is a sequence of data, and the linked list is a sequence of data linked with each other.
